### Phase 5 — scoring view
Read: ONTOLOGY.md §Scoring.
Deliverables: pure function
  S_θ(t) = clip[-10,10]( Σ_i  p_i · s_i · λ^((t−t_i)/h) · ν_i )
  with h = forward_horizon/2; novelty discount ν_i = 0.15 when claim i has
  embedding cosine > 0.88 to a prior same-institution claim on the same
  theme (cross-institution repeats keep ν = 1.0); per-institution net
  contribution capped at ±3 per theme; breadth B_θ = count of distinct
  institutions with net-positive contribution. All constants module-level
  and named.
Gates:
  - `test_score_order_invariance` (property): S invariant under ledger
    append-order permutation at fixed timestamps.
  - `test_novelty_and_caps`: golden repeat-claim case → discounted;
    synthetic single-institution flood → capped at ±3.
  - `test_score_is_pure`: two calls at same as_of → identical; no state
    mutated (assert via ledger row-count and hash before/after).

### Phase 6 — orphan clustering + admission
Read: ONTOLOGY.md §Admission.
Deliverables: orphan clustering (mechanism-tag + embedding); admission
  rule: ≥3 claims, ≥2 institutions, within 30 days → CandidateTheme
  (CANDIDATE status) synthesized over the node vocabulary and passed
  through WF; CANDIDATE→ACTIVE requires B ≥ 2 and |S| ≥ 2. Out-of-vocab
  node proposals route to a REVIEW queue (never auto-added).
Gate: `test_end_to_end_golden`: full pipeline parse→extract→map→score→
  admit over the 5-doc corpus → assert exact expected_registry.json
  end-state, including the failing-admission cluster remaining in the
  orphan pool.

### Phase 7 — wiki renderer + drift detection
Read: ONTOLOGY.md §Rendered view.
Deliverables: renderer producing per-theme pages (mechanism chain, axis,
  S_θ and B_θ, falsifier + Breach Buffer state, per-institution evidence
  table, event-log timeline); parser recovering structured fields from a
  rendered page; nightly drift-diff job emitting proposed ThemeEvents
  (provenance="analyst") into a REVIEW queue — never auto-applied.
Gate: `test_render_parse_roundtrip`: fold → render → parse → recovered
  ThemeHypothesis equals folded original, for every theme in the golden
  end-state registry.

